         <abstract>
            <p>For certain lattice rules of `rank 2' it has been shown, in a recent paper, that a unique representation exists in a form suitable for computer evaluation. The present paper describes computer searches of such rules, reports results and identifies rules that appear promising for the numerical evaluation of practical multidimensional integrals.</p>
          </abstract>
